tions about the difference between statutory and mandatory training. We have selected a few of these questions and answered them below.</span></p><div class="sc-furwcr eAonsE pf-306_ pf-icon-right" data-scrolling="false" data-multiple="false" data-pf-type="Accordion"><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-pVTFL cZzoXH pf-307_"><button type="button" class="sc-gKclnd gImmvL pf-308_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="b25a8cc0-9109-4dad-9158-588c3bdae961" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-plus pfa-arrow"></i><span>What is CSTF aligned statutory and mandatory training?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="b25a8cc0-9109-4dad-9158-588c3bdae961" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-iCfMLu ewKYhD pf-310_"><p class="sc-fIosxK hdNOer pf-311_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cLpAjG dTtSfA pf-313_">CSTF aligned statutory and mandatory training is compulsory training determined under the UK Core Skills Training Framework ( UK CSTF) as essential for the safe and efficient delivery of healthcare services. Healthcare statutory and mandatory training is designed to reduce organisational risks and comply with current UK legislation, national guidance and local policies.
<br><br>The UK Core Skills Training Framework (CSTF) sets out 11 statutory and mandatory training topics for all staff working in health and social care settings. The CSTF includes nationally agreed learning outcomes and training delivery standards.
